wine
In order for a good grapevine to ripen to perfection it needs nutrient-rich soil, a good
geographical position and weather conditions as well as lots of care and attention.
Winemaking demands purity, in depth knowledge and the creative imagination of the
cellarmaster. When creating our wine list, we take care that only the typical, expressive
wines that conform to these rigorous demands are selected.

What could be better, when enjoying artistically served light cuisine, harmonious, noble
drops of wine and inspiring music, than to think of clear mountain streams in radiant
sunshine, the fresh smells of spring and lush green mountain meadows...
No pleasure is temporary, for the impression it leaves behind endures!'
as Johann Wolfgang von Goethe once noted.
